We took a look at the top 1000 cards, then look at the _average value of the deck_ that card is in. Then we looked at the average deck price of all the decks in that color identity. If you subtract those, you can see if that card is played in more budget lists or more expensive lists.
So for example, if   Cancel's average deck price of decks in it is  $200, and the average deck with U in the color identity is $300, cancel is seen in much cheaper decks
so for example, here specifically. If a deck has cancel in it, it'll generally be $565 cheaper than the average deck.
